        "@value": "\n        \nBurnstick\n\n    \nFri, Mar 12, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nRosthern, SK – @ Station Arts Centre Cooperative\nPresented by Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\n\n\n\nBuilt on emotion-stirring storytelling and unmistakable vocal harmonies accompanied by a century-old instrument, Burnstick, a JUNO nominated husband and wife Folk duo, are intent on creating affecting music that inspires listeners to feel. The Manitoba based Indigenous duo features Nadia and Jason Burnstick, esteemed independent artists who united over a decade ago to create deeply moving, cinematic Folk music using their trademark vocal pairing, and Jason's mastery of the lap slide Weissenborn guitar. Backed by their drummer, Tony Raybould, Nadia and Jason perform deeply resonant music that strikes a chord with audiences. With thought-provoking lyrics and engaging stories, they leave listeners reflecting on their\nown experiences, feelings, and memories.\n\n\nFolk • Bluegrass • Americana\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nTue, Nov 24, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nMacklin, SK - Macklin Credit Union Legacy Center\n\nPresented by Macklin Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Nov 25, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nShellbrook, SK - Shellbrook Theatre\n\nPresented by Shellbrook & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Nov 26, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nRegina, SK - Darke Hall\n\nPresented by Darke Hall Society Inc.\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Nov 27, 2026 @ 7:00 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nYorkton, SK - St. Andrew's United Church - Yorkton\n\nPresented by Yorkton Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Nov 28, 2026 @ 8:00 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nLangenburg, SK - George Layh Theatre\n\nPresented by Langenburg Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Mar 12, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nRosthern, SK - Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\nPresented by Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Mar 13, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nSwift Current, SK - Event Centre\n\nPresented by Swift Current Arts Council\n\n\n\n    