  {
    "@id": "https://www.osac.ca/temporary/6a2d293e-6fb5-4b0e-8786-40bfc1fbd850",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/Article"
    ],
    "https://schema.org/inLanguage": [
      {
        "@value": "en-GB"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/articleBody": [
      {
        "@value": "\n        \nDuo Octavian: Carson Becke and Suren Barry - The Planets in Black and White\n\n    \nSun, Sep 13, 2026 @ 3:00 pm\nRegina, SK – @ Darke Hall\nPresented by Regina Musical Club\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\n\nGustav Holst’s The Planets is one of the most iconic large orchestral works of all time, creating a sound world that inspired cinematic composers like John Williams and Hans Zimmer.  In this concert, you’ll hear the The Planets like you’ve never heard them before, in a new concert arrangement for two pianos by Duo Octavian.  Also on the program is Kelly-Marie Murphy’s Dr. Blue’s Rapidly Deployable Escape Ladder, commissioned by Duo Octavian in 2022, and Suren Barry’s arrangement of Rameau’s characterful overture to the opera Pygmalion.\n\n\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nSun, Sep 13, 2026 @ 3:00 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nRegina, SK - Darke Hall\n\nPresented by Regina Musical Club\n\n\n\n    "
      }
