    "https://schema.org/articleBody": [
      {
        "@value": "\n        \nJessica Rhaye with Preeper and MacKay\n\n    \nFri, Apr 9, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nSwift Current, SK – @ Event Centre\nPresented by Swift Current Arts Council\n\n\n\n\nJessica Rhaye with Bill Preeper and Sandy MacKay is a folk trio that back to the height of the Greenwich Village folk scene of the 60’s, weaving and sharing lead and harmony. It's new folk music at its finest, pulling together inspiration from the likes of Woody Guthrie, Ian Tyson, Bob Dylan, with a Maritime Appalachian Folk sound with a unique mix of acoustic and electric instruments. The trio’s version of Blowin’ in the Wind has generated, to date, more than 15 million views on YouTube. \"The modern folk trio offered their skills to the famed Dylan track (Blowin’ in the Wind) in a string laden rendition. Rich with golden vocals, acoustics and even a Mandolin, Rhaye, and her group would make Baez and the rest of the ‘60-s decade proud with this heartfelt version.+- AMERICAN SONGWRITER MAGAZINE\n\n\nFolk • Bluegrass • Americana\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Apr 9, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nSwift Current, SK - Event Centre\n\nPresented by Swift Current Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Apr 10, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nAssiniboia, SK - Prince of Wales Cultural & Recreation Centre\n\nPresented by Assiniboia & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nTue, Apr 13, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nBiggar, SK - Majestic Theatre\n\nPresented by Biggar & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Apr 14, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nMacklin, SK - Macklin Credit Union Legacy Center\n\nPresented by Macklin Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Apr 15, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nRosthern, SK - Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\nPresented by Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Apr 16, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nNipawin, SK - Evergreen Centre\n\nPresented by Nipawin Performing Arts Group\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Apr 17, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nHumboldt, SK - Humboldt and District Gallery\n\nPresented by Humboldt Area Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nTue, Apr 20, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nWatrous, SK - Watrous Civic Centre\n\nPresented by Watrous and Area Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Apr 21, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nPreeceville, SK - Preeceville Legion Hall\n\nPresented by Whitehawk Arts Council Inc.\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Apr 22, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nTicket Info\n\n\n\nMoosomin, SK - Moosomin Community Theatre\n\nPresented by Moosomin & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Apr 23, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nKipling, SK - Kipling Community Centre\n\nPresented by Kipling & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n    "
      }
