        "@value": "\n        \nLaila Biali\n\n      \nFri, Feb 5, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nRegina, SK – @ Darke Hall\nPresented by Darke Hall Society Inc.\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\n\nMulti-award winning vocalist, pianist, songwriter and national radio host Laila Biali is thrilled to share her latest tribute project, Joni Mitchell & the Canadian Songbook Reimagined - a memorable concert experience filled with dynamic covers of our country's musical icons. Audiences will be treated to fresh takes on a range of Canadian artists from across the decades including Leonard Cohen, Neil Young, k.d. Lang, Bruce Cockburn, Sarah McLachlan and many more, all centred around the heart of this show: prairie royalty, Joni Mitchell.\n\nCome experience why the Washington Post hails Biali for her unique ability to \"masterfully mix jazz and pop\", interweaving your favourite Canadian classics with playful anecdotes and heartwarming stories.\n\n\nJazz/Blues\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Feb 4, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nPrince Albert, SK - E.A. Rawlinson Centre\n\nPresented by E.A. Rawlinson Centre\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Feb 5, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nRegina, SK - Darke Hall\n\nPresented by Darke Hall Society Inc.\n\n\n\n    "
