    "https://schema.org/inLanguage": [
      {
        "@value": "en-GB"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/articleBody": [
      {
        "@value": "\n        \nLast Birds\n\n     \nSat, Jan 30, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nMacklin, SK – @ Macklin Credit Union Legacy Center\nPresented by Macklin Arts Council\n\n\n\n\nLast Birds’ intimate, one mic performance style blends contemporary folk and traditional country music. Through haunting vocal harmonies and interwoven acoustic guitars, the duo tells stories of small-town experiences and the challenges of prairie life. Mike Davis and Lindsay Arnold draw audiences into a shared experience with their honest lyrics and authentic spousal banter that is satisfyingly bittersweet, often humorous, and always mesmerizing to watch.\n\n\nFolk • Bluegrass • Americana\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Jan 21, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nSturgis, SK - Sturgis Community Hall\n\nPresented by Whitehawk Arts Council Inc.\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Jan 22, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nTisdale, SK - Maurice Taylor Performing Arts Theatre\n\nPresented by Tisdale Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Jan 23, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nHumboldt, SK - Humboldt and District Gallery\n\nPresented by Humboldt Area Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Jan 29, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nSwift Current, SK - Event Centre\n\nPresented by Swift Current Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Jan 30, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nMacklin, SK - Macklin Credit Union Legacy Center\n\nPresented by Macklin Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Mar 18, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nCanora, SK - Canora Composite School\n\nPresented by Canora Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Mar 19, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nHudson Bay, SK - St. Stephen's United Church - Hudson Bay\n\nPresented by Hudson Bay Allied Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Mar 20, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nKipling, SK - Kipling Community Centre\n\nPresented by Kipling & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n    "
      }
    ],
