  },
  {
    "@id": "https://www.osac.ca/temporary/c0e091de-8e8f-441b-b7da-910e20d56d95",
    "@type": [
      "https://schema.org/Article"
    ],
    "https://schema.org/inLanguage": [
      {
        "@value": "en-GB"
      }
    ],
    "https://schema.org/articleBody": [
      {
        "@value": "\n        \nMaggie’s Wake\n\n     \nFri, Apr 9, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nIndian Head, SK – @ Grand Theatre\nPresented by Indian Head Theatre and Community Arts Inc.\n\n\n\n\n2025 Canadian Folk Music Award winners Maggie's Wake are a high energy, “new trad” female-fronted folk-celtic crew from London, who are creating an exciting splash in the roots music scene!  Fresh off their acclaimed debut at Ireland’s premier music industry showcase, Maggie’s Wake are back on home soil, touring their fiery fusion of Celtic tradition and roots swagger. Expect driving jigs'n'reels, soaring whistles, double fiddle, flashes of country twang not to mention Cajun/global roots twists that’s pure joy from start to finish.\nDale Watson, the Texas honky tonk legend, says \"You can't grow if you rip your roots out of the ground\" and Maggie's Wake have taken that to heart. They are honouring tradition while forging their own path in folk music.\nThe acclaimed band features award-winning songwriter/multi-instrumentalist, Tara Dunphy and award-winning violinist/fiddler/songwriter Lindsay Schindler, backed by the stellar musicianship of Andrew Kosty on bass and Kenneth Palmer on guitar.\n\n\nFolk • Bluegrass • Americana\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Apr 9, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nIndian Head, SK - Grand Theatre\n\nPresented by Indian Head Theatre and Community Arts Inc.\n\n\n\n    "
      }
    ],
