        "@value": "\n        \nThe Fugitives\n\n     \nThu, Apr 29, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\nBiggar, SK – @ Majestic Theatre\nPresented by Biggar & District Arts Council\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\n\nA Canadian folk staple, The Fugitives have been nominated for a JUNO, as well as 7 Canadian Folk Music Awards, including Best Vocal Group, Best Ensemble, and Best Songwriter. They've performed at Glastonbury, were awarded Best Folk Album of the Year by the German Music Critics’ Association, and were named a 2020 Globe & Mail \"Top Arts Pick of the Year\". They've earned a reputation for unforgettable live shows, brimming with complex harmonies, infectious storytelling and top-notch musicianship. As the CBC has it: \"This show is simply brilliant.\" In 2026-27, they will be touring in support of their seventh album.\n\n\nFolk • Bluegrass • Americana\n\nWatch Video:\n\nAppearances\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Oct 21, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nAssiniboia, SK - Prince of Wales Cultural & Recreation Centre\n\nPresented by Assiniboia & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Oct 22, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nKindersley, SK - Norman Ritchie Community Centre\n\nPresented by Kindersley & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Oct 23, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nWatrous, SK - Watrous Civic Centre\n\nPresented by Watrous and Area Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Oct 24, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nNipawin, SK - Evergreen Centre\n\nPresented by Nipawin Performing Arts Group\n\n\n\n\n\nTue, Oct 27, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nHumboldt, SK - Humboldt and District Gallery\n\nPresented by Humboldt Area Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Oct 28, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nTicket Info\n\n\n\nMoosomin, SK - Moosomin Community Theatre\n\nPresented by Moosomin & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Oct 29, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nCanora, SK - Canora Composite School\n\nPresented by Canora Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Oct 30, 2026 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nMoose Jaw, SK - Mae Wilson Theatre\n\nPresented by Moose Jaw Cultural Centre\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, Apr 24, 2027 @ 8:00 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nLangenburg, SK - George Layh Theatre\n\nPresented by Langenburg Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nMon, Apr 26, 2027 @ 7:00 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nYorkton, SK - Anne Portnuff Theatre, Yorkton Regional High School\n\nPresented by Yorkton Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nTue, Apr 27, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nEstevan, SK - Orpheum Theatre\n\nPresented by Estevan Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nWed, Apr 28, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nSwift Current, SK - Event Centre\n\nPresented by Swift Current Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nThu, Apr 29, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nBiggar, SK - Majestic Theatre\n\nPresented by Biggar & District Arts Council\n\n\n\n\n\nFri, Apr 30, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\n\n\n\nRosthern, SK - Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\nPresented by Station Arts Centre Cooperative\n\n\n\n\n\nSat, May 1, 2027 @ 7:30 pm\n\n\nBuy Tickets\n\n\n\nTisdale, SK - Maurice Taylor Performing Arts Theatre\n\nPresented by Tisdale Arts Council\n\n\n\n    "
